Subject: Re: [T2] Westy need seatbelts in NJ?

At 03:01 PM 7/13/2004 -0400, Tom wrote:
>Since the inside of a westy is much like a camper, are
>seatbelts neccessary?

If you want to carry passengers back there, then yes, they are necessary.

>My 73 has none besides the driver and passenger front
>seats, no belts in the back.

But it DOES have seatbelt mounting points.  They are hidden under
white or black plastic, large, Phillips head bolts.

I went to a wrecking yard, and looking only in modern Audi and VW
cars, got several sets of back seat seatbelts.  The retractable parts
I used on the front seats, and the middle seat seatbelts, on the
two "seats" on the folding bed.

